1.title: Rage
1.plot: Sasha's anger is provoked when a familiar face from her past arrives at Ashdene Ridge.

2.title: Five Doors
2.plot: Jody and the YP band together to investigate the truth behind Sasha's criminal actions.

3.title: The Lone Ranger
3.plot: Alex is pushed to the brink when he's blindsided by the return of his mother.

4.title: Face Your Fear
4.plot: Ryan's fear of failure threatens to overwhelm him when he volunteers at a stables.

5.title: Run the Risk
5.plot: Tyler's prank call to the radio station has catastrophic consequences.

6.title: Candi-Rose?
6.plot: Candi-Rose's secret past comes to light when she tracks down someone special to her.

7.title: The Return of the Freaky Twins
7.plot: Floss' world is rocked when she concludes that Ross must be her real brother.

8.title: Snake
8.plot: Chloe vows revenge when she's overlooked for a trip to the cinema.

9.title: Three's A Crowd
9.plot: Sasha's jealously simmers when she discovers that Josh has a new girlfriend.

1.title: Freedom Part 1: Home Alone
1.plot: The kids are excited to be left home alone, but is it as easy as it seems?

2.title: Freedom Part 2: Liberty in the DG
2.plot: Still without Mike and Gina, the children soon realise that they are unable to fend for themselves and end up turning against each other. Having spent all of their money, the residents face starvation with the fridge devoured of all its contents. and Elektra takes charge, and will do anything to get what she wants.

3.title: Baby
3.plot: When her dad's pregnant girlfriend moves into their flat, Lily rebels, telling Mike she wants to come back to the Dumping Ground.

4.title: S.O.S.
4.plot: Jody seems happy to be back with her family, but Carmen soon discovers she lives in fear of her brother and plots a rescue mission. Meanwhile, Gus teaches Tyler Morse-Code, been as Tyler hasn't got a phone.

5.title: What Would Gus Want?
5.plot: A couple want to foster Gus but will Gus what to live with them?

6.title: The Real Faith Davis
6.plot: Wicked whispers fly when the police come to see Faith, who will not say why. And new girl Floss wonders where on earth she has been dumped.

7.title: The Truth Is Out There
7.plot: After bad exam results, Frank denounces school and gets himself a job in a cafe. There, he falls for the waitress, Jade, who introduces him to a psychic. Is he being taken for a ride?

8.title: Dreamland
8.plot: Rick's dad turns up full of promises about a happy family future. But is he still a con man at heart? Meanwhile, Gina's mum, Hattie, turns up and Tee thinks that Mike wants Hattie in a home. Not knowing that Hattie has dementia.

9.title: A Day in the Past
9.plot: It is the day of the Dumping Ground's annual day out and the Young People get to be Edwardians for the day. However, the day is not fun when Johnny is in charge.

10.title: Oh Mo!
10.plot: Mo is the Dumping Ground's quirky new resident and everyone thinks he's extremely odd, especially Tyler who he must share with. So Tee decides to take Mo under her wing with inevitable consequences as Mo pushes her to the limit.

11.title: Seriously Funny
11.plot: When a big practical joke backfires, Tyler decides it is time that he grew up. But Elektra seeking for revenge after being victim to Tyler's prank, starts to bully Tyler. Meanwhile, Lily, Carmen and Tee fall out at an unsupervised sleepover at Lily's flat. Have they grown apart?

12.title: Esme
12.plot: Carmen meets a fabulous girl named Esme in a shoe shop. But when Esme asks something impossible of Carmen, will she do it? Or will she stay at Elm Tree House and uncover the problem going on there?

13.title: Scary Beasts
13.plot: A face from the past comes back to haunt Faith and brings danger to the Dumping Ground. And Mo buys a 'magic' egg which unexpectedly hatches into what Johnny and Elektra believe is a venomous snake.

0.title: Jody in Wonderland
0.plot: Jody had a angry moment in Mike's office then suddenly a rabbit appeared and Jody followed it in a world she never be there before.

1.title: Booting Up Part One: Kick Off
1.plot: Bailey Wharton is the DG's newest resident but when attempting to run away, Faith spots him but gets run over by a car when trying to catch up with him. Meanwhile, Mike questions Frank about life in his new flat.

2.title: Booting Up Part Two: Quitters
2.plot: After being run over by a car, Faith struggles to adjust to being in a wheelchair, and takes her frustration out on the younger residents by bullying them. And Bailey runs away with his dad when he turns up at the DG.

3.title: The Dumping Ground Experience
3.plot: When a filmmaker, Sasha, comes to Ashdene Ridge to make a training film for future care workers, Jody notices that everybody's behaving like mindless zombies, overcome with fame. So she decides to take things into her own hands, and calls on a friend to help her out.

4.title: The Barbecue
4.plot: Lily must break the news to Carmen that she is moving to Brighton with her family. Carmen, in frustration, kicks Bailey's football hard and smashes Johnny's bedroom window. Bailey gets the blame, but Floss saw Carmen kick the ball.

5.title: Finding Frank
5.plot: Frank has gone missing, as he hasn't been seen for weeks. Some of the residents later discover that Frank is living on the streets, after he is conned and it serious debt.

6.title: Holding On
6.plot: Expectations are high when Tyler's mum comes for a visit.

7.title: Endurance
7.plot: The DG kids split into two groups - Team Talent Show and Team Footie - and embark on a crazy endurance challenge, involving who can stay touching the telly the longest, to decide who will win the right to watch their favourite programme.

8.title: I Have a Dream
8.plot: An unlikely friendship is formed when Mo realizes that Bailey has dyslexia. And with a writing competition going on, they decide to team up to write a short story. And Rick and Faith are at logger heads with each other.

9.title: Sticks and Stones
9.plot: Bailey's dreams are thrown into jeopardy when his football coach shows his true colours after saying a racist comment to Bailey.

10.title: GI Johnny
10.plot: When Johnny tackles a mugger, he realises what he wants to do in life. Join the army. But is he really prepared to go to war and leave all his friends (and most importantly, his sister Tee) behind?

11.title: Be My Girl
11.plot: Floss meets some prospective parents, but isn't too keen on them, and Rick and Carmen's friendship reaches breaking point when they become more than just friends.

12.title: Hope
12.plot: Tee and Johnny's world is turned upside down when they receive a letter from their mum. Meanwhile homeless girl Kazima moves into the Dumping Ground, and Mike has to break the news to Carmen that she's sharing her bedroom with Kazima.

13.title: Face the Music
13.plot: Frank lets his anger get the better of him when he bumps into Liam during his first day at work, which causes him to lose his own job as well as Faith's. Liam has been ignoring Frank for the past year, but can they become friends again?

14.title: Liam's Story
14.plot: Liam O'Donovan's life is just as chaotic now as it was in the Dumping Ground. Liam struggles to study plumbing at collage as it's not what he wants to do. He would rather work in the music industry, but does he have a future in music?

1.title: Law & Disorder Part One: Party Games
1.plot: A party for new foster parents goes very wrong, as Bailey and Carmen battle out over celebrity parents. After watery sabotage unearths stolen purses and wallets , sinister new resident Ryan arrives and turns detective showing he doesn't care how far he will go to get what he wants

2.title: Law & Disorder Part Two: Grand Theft DG
2.plot: There has been a burglary at the DG and new resident Ryan is at the ready to work out who did it.

3.title: Stuck with You
3.plot: Carmen and Jody get handcuffed together by floss and Carmen and Jody has 2 different things to do Jody wants to go to a book signing Carmen wants to go to a party What do they do in the end? They have two new girls in the dumping ground they find the key and they try and hide it a again so they get a big reward

4.title: Mischief
4.plot: When Bailey bumps into a homeless man who later dies, he feels guilty, and decides to become the new owner of his dog Mischief. However Mischief proves difficult to train, and as Bailey is doubting his philosophy of always trying, Ryan who has a phobia of dogs sets Mischief free, with disastrous consequences - as Mischief is taken to the vet after being hit by a car.

5.title: Now You See Me
5.plot: Tee finds herself lured into the world of street art by a homeless artist.

6.title: It's Not About the Money
6.plot: Tyler is upset that Bailey got new football boots but he isn't allowed a new magic trick, Ryan knows a way to get money so that Tyler can buy one himself; they plan to fake a burglary in the Dumping Ground. All this happens on a big day for someone. But does this go according to plan? Of course not.

7.title: Fake It to Make It
7.plot: Carmen gets a chance to be a TV presenter and impress a celebrity.

8.title: Breaking In
8.plot: The residents of The Dumping Ground head off on a day trip to a theme park. There aren't enough tickets for everyone though, so Tee and Kazima go to a holiday club instead. Bored at the club, they sneak off home to The Dumping Ground, only to come face to face with thieves. Can Tee and Kazima win their game of cat and mouse, and stop the thieves from finding their money?

9.title: The Long Way Home
9.plot: When things are going wrong in Harry's foster placement, it falls to Ryan to rescue him.

10.title: Dragon Slayer
10.plot: After Johnny's Stepfather has been released from prison its up to him to protect Tee.

11.title: Three Days
11.plot: A new girl called Sasha stops off on her way to a secure home.

12.title: Free to Good Home
12.plot: Sasha's naughty little brother Dexter arrives and gets her into trouble.

13.title: Better Than You
13.plot: Bailey attempts to pass his review meeting and get tickets to Wembley.

14.title: Who Are You?
14.plot: Tee decides to look into Ryan's past to discredit him at his birthday party.

15.title: Where Is Love?
15.plot: Mo gets the lead in the school play, but his delight is short-lived when his dad falls ill

16.title: Goodbye Girl
16.plot: Tyler's plan to put on a great magic show leads him to a first love.

17.title: Something Borrowed
17.plot: Carmen drops May-Li's valuable antique necklace down the toilet.

18.title: What Matters?
18.plot: Tee enlists the twins help to prove she can be a party animal.

19.title: Coming Round
19.plot: After Jody upsets Ryan, he sees his chance to take revenge during a martial arts battle.

20.title: Refuge
20.plot: The immigration authorities want to send Kazima back to Somalia.

1.title: Lost and Found
1.plot: Bailey's world is rocked when his mum turns up at Ashdene Ridge and he questions whether he can forgive her for abandoning him as a toddler. Meanwhile, Carmen resorts to drastic measures when Ofsted inspectors arrive unexpectedly.

2.title: Bear-Faced Liar
2.plot: Bailey has to break some bad news to his mum - but what is she hiding from him? And what has it got to do with the Shakespeare play the young people are staging? Meanwhile Mike and May-Li continue to stress about the Ofstead inspectors.

3.title: Stepping Up
3.plot: Jody, Carmen and Tee want to perform a dance in front of the care kids and things seem to be breaking around ashdene ridge!

4.title: They Walk Among Us
4.plot: Mo is certain that aliens exist, so goes on the hunt to find one, and almost succedes. Once he does, he's not too keen on the thought of sending him back, but is he really from outer space? Tee bumps into the boy of her dreams whilst in the park and she convinces him that she's a sport fanatic.

5.title: Hold the Front Page
5.plot: Ryan receives a letter from his sister and runs upstairs with it, causing Finn to trip and fall, as he comes down. However, everyone believes Ryan pushed him. When Chloe turns up at the DG, Ryan feels nervous about meeting her for the first time since her accident. Certain he did something to put her in a wheelchair, Tee and Sasha spy on them while they speak. But it is revealed they got the wrong end of the stick. Meanwhile, Tyler wins a journalism competition. Chloe leaves Ashdene Ridge, promising to visit again.

6.title: Growing Pains
6.plot: Tee gets a taste of what life outside care might be like when she goes for her first college interview. However, sparks fly between her and Carmen when neither of their days go according to plan.

7.title: Submarine
7.plot: Unsure of where she fits in, Sasha's glad when an old friend seems to show an interest in her. But does he really have her best interests at heart? Meanwhile, Carmen and Tee realise that they forgot Kazima's birthday. But when they throw a surprise party for her, they don't get the reaction they were expecting.

8.title: First Past the Post
8.plot: Election fever strikes the Dumping Ground as Tyler and Floss battle it out over a place on a forum for children in care. However, Ryan sees the chaos that erupts as a chance to settle an old score.

9.title: Survivors
9.plot: Everyone's missing Mike, so Kazima suggests a trip out to raise the young people's spirits. However, it is not long before they get lost in the countryside. Meanwhile, Ryan starts to wonder if he's gone too far.

10.title: The End of It All
10.plot: As the chances of saving Mike is slipping, will Ryan step up to the mark and save the favourite care worker?

11.title: Perfect Match
11.plot: Upset by a surprise her mum springs on her, Sasha asks to be put up for fostering - but she is shocked when she learns a couple want to adopt her.

12.title: Doris
12.plot: When Carmen opens a makeshift salon in the Dumping Ground garage, she gets Doris, a sharp-tongued pensioner, as her first customer.

13.title: Risky Business
13.plot: Bailey's business is on the road to success when he joins forces with a friendly rival in a Young Entrepreneur competition. But he's about to find out that business and pleasures don't necessarily mix.

14.title: Troll
14.plot: Fearing she is being overlooked, Floss has an idea that will put her centre stage. But is she so desperate for the limelight that she will forget her friends?

15.title: It Takes Two
15.plot: New boy Sammy starts to get on people's nerves, and Tyler steps in to defend him. Grateful Sammy is determined to impress his new friend but just how far is he prepared to go? Meanwhile Ryan's sister Chloe moves in, but Ryan ends up becoming a bit too over-protective of his younger sister.

16.title: Getting to Know You
16.plot: Tyler's delighted at the prospect of a new future with his mum - but, after years apart, they soon find out they have a lot to learn about one another. Meanwhile everyone is taking Tyler's decision to move in with his mum badly, causing Tyler to loose his friends. Meanwhile Mo develops his first crush with a young girl called Kara.

17.title: Two Camps
17.plot: The young people decide to have an Ashdene Ridge festival. Ryan tells Joseph about a prank he pulled and Carmen chooses to go glamping. Whilst putting the tent up, Joseph steals a tent piece, causing the tent to collapse. Tee and Sasha find out Joseph took it and Ryan and Chloe overhear Tee and Sasha talking about Ryan. Ryan admits to Chloe he was told ghost stories by an older child when he was taken into care. Tee and Sasha return the piece for the tent and Chloe tells Tee and Sasha what Ryan said. Tee and Sasha scare Ryan with a ghost story. Ryan finds Chloe's ...

18.title: How to Be Perfect
18.plot: When Kazima starts behaving strangely, her friends don't understand what's got into her. Then the truth emerges, and Kazima reveals if May-Li adopts her, then she'll have more of a chance of not being deported, this leads to the others getting jealous and causes the Dumping Ground to fall apart. Meanwhile, Joseph "kidnaps" Mischief to teach Bailey a lesson after laughing at Tyler, wanting to learn how to dance to impress a girl. But Joseph's plan backfires when Mischief goes missing for real. And when Tyler fails to learn any dancing from Mike, he turns to Floss.

19.title: One for Sorrow
19.plot: It's Carmen and Tee's last day at the Dumping Ground, and no one wants them to go. But they are in for more of a bad day when they are told they're no longer being housed together, and things start to go missing in the DG.

20.title: Two for Joy
20.plot: Jody finds out that following your heart can lead to danger when Kingsley is released from prison - will her friends be able to save her? Or will Jody's life come to a fiery end? Meanwhile, Ryan confesses his darkest secret when an independent visitor comes to talk to him. Meanwhile Billie, Toni, Floss and Finn decide to raise sponsor money to get a donkey named after them.

21.title: Floss the Foundling
21.plot: When Floss has to do the vacuuming. she ruins a picture that Tyler, Mo, Billie and Toni work on when they don't want her help. Floss falls asleep on the sofa and ends up in the Foundling Hospital. She encounters Hetty Feather, who introduces Floss to the Foundling Hospital ways. Sheila and Elizabeth are mean towards Floss and Hetty gets Floss out of trouble with Matron Bottomley. Floss and Hetty make friends. When Floss wakes up, she draws a replacement picture.

1.title: Miscreants, Robots and Bullies
1.plot: Dexter's desire to be with Bailey puts him at odds with Sasha and a former Football Academy rival, Roddy. Meanwhile, the Umblebys move in next door.

2.title: Back in the Game
2.plot: Sasha and Bailey ally to save Dexter. The YP try to build bridges with the Umblebys, but first impressions aren't easy to change.

3.title: One Giant Leap
3.plot: Ryan overhears a conversation between Mike and May-Li and thinks he is being kicked out the DG. Meanwhile Joseph and Finn try to find proof that the moon landing wasn't faked.

4.title: The Fairytale Princess
4.plot: Chloe meets Candi-Rose, but is their friendship doomed to fail? Kazima's charity cake bake is dealt a blow by downtrodden neighbor Edward.

5.title: Sittin in a Tree
5.plot: Jody reacts badly to the assumption that she and Tyler are seen as a couple by all the others, and sets out to find him a girlfriend.

6.title: Faking It
6.plot: A moment in the limelight beckons for Floss when she wins a part in a commercial. However, acting with her on-screen mother scares her.

7.title: Sasha Bellman P.I.
7.plot: Sasha turns PI when a parcel disappears but the quest for justice uncovers unpleasant truths.

8.title: Belief
8.plot: Kazima's kindness is put to the test when she meets a troubled homeless teenager.

9.title: Vox Populi
9.plot: A radio internship gives Tyler a big story, but the truth is not always what it seems. Finn encounters a 'hobgoblin'.

10.title: Free
10.plot: Kazima prepares for a college meeting, hoping to do engineering, but Alex turns up. Kazima threatens to phone the police, but he tells her that George is in a bad way.

11.title: The Wardrobe
11.plot: A wardrobe carrying an ancient curse brings trouble for Ryan, Joseph and Kazima.

12.title: Farvel
12.plot: Kaz finds out where her dad is and her dad says that her brother isn't found so she leaves the dumping ground and finds her brother and they are all reunited

13.title: Choose Your Own Adventure
13.plot: After Mike declares that The Dumping Ground is on a tech ban for a week, Floss seeks out adventure but her curiosity leads her into danger. Meanwhile, Alex continues to struggle to fit in, and Ryan isn't helping him feel any better.

14.title: Making Waves
14.plot: While everyone else goes to the beach for the day, Jody and May-Li has to stay at home to greet the new arrival at Ashdene Ridge, Taz, who's got a bad temper. After many attempts to make Taz feel welcome, Jody starts to lose her patients.

15.title: The Phantom of Ashdene Ridge
15.plot: It's Halloween at The Dumping Ground, and there's a ghost about. And is the new night manager Mimi Blunt all she seems?

16.title: The Switch
16.plot: A couple comes forward to adopt the twins, but Toni doesn't share Billie's enthusiasm about the chance for a fresh start. Meanwhile Jody and Sasha clash when they're forced to share a bedroom.

17.title: Mission Totally Possible
17.plot: Mike and Jody embark on an elaborate plan to retrieve Jody's phone, which has been locked up after tricking Mike.

18.title: Sick
18.plot: When Sasha gets locked in the bathroom, her liberation comes in the form of Josh and she experiences her first love interest. Meanwhile, Floss is experiencing the first stages of puberty.

19.title: Rough Justice
19.plot: There's been a theft at the Dumping Ground. Jody and Joseph are the prime suspects, but who is guilty? Charlie sets up a Kangaroo Court to come to a decision. Meanwhile, Alex's secrets from his past are exposed.

20.title: Where You Belong
20.plot: When Mike and May-Li's working relationship is pushed to breaking point, the YP must go to extreme lengths to fix it.

21.title: #SaveTheDG
21.plot: Residents old and new must come together to Save The DG. The future of The Dumping Ground is in jeopardy. Some familiar faces are coming back to help save their old home. Tee, Johnny, Perhaps Elektra and Frank.

22.title: What Lies Beneath
22.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

23.title: Dumping Ground Island
23.plot: Tyler's fear of reality takes him to a desert island where he must face his fears.

1.title: Jody on the Ropes
1.plot: Jody's anger boils over when she's forced to play happy families with her mum to impress her new boyfriend, Grant. Too ashamed to admit to her new lover her child's in care, she orders Jody to pretend she's not. Jody eventually has enough of her mum's charade, Denise gives her an ultimatum:fix things or she'll disown her. Again.

2.title: Saved by the Bell
2.plot: The pressure rises on Jody as she's torn between a future with her mum or one at Ashdene Ridge. She flips and inadvertently injures Archie. It's a step too far for Mike and May-Li and Jody's place at the DG comes under threat. Running away with nowhere else to turn, Jody sleeps rough.

3.title: Give and Take
3.plot: Feeling forgotten about and being left out, Candi-Rose looks to boost her popularity with her knowledge of shopping. She impresses the YP and but soon becomes overwhelmed by demands for the latest items and resorts to shoplifting.

4.title: Heroes
4.plot: Saddened to hear that his friend doesn't want a birthday party, Finn sets out to change Alex's mind with the help of Charlie, and his imaginary dad, Billy.

5.title: SorryNotSorry
5.plot: Today's the day that Sasha leaves Ashdene Ridge and returns home. Full of enthusiasm, Sasha records her last day for her vlog interviewing the others. With a chipped bone in her toe, Floss decides to milk the injury for all that it's worth.

6.title: Cat's in the Cradle
6.plot: A chance encounter puts Alex face to face with a woman he believes to be his mum. Full of emotion, Alex has a million questions. With the help of Charlie, Alex goes digging but is in for another shock when he meets his mum's daughter Alice.

7.title: Challenging Times
7.plot: It's competition time as Ashdene Ridge takes on rival care home Graybridge. Charlie's competitive side shows after Emi and Amelie from Graybridge draw her in. Meanwhile, Mike's shocked to see ex-girlfriend Fiona back in his life.

8.title: Two Sides to Every Story
8.plot: Feeling threatened by May-Li and the other YP, Jay resorts to drastic measures to protect his brother. Jay accuses May-Li of hitting him. With May-Li's career put on the line, the YP are determined to get the truth out of Jay before it's too late.

9.title: Utopia
9.plot: With the YP constantly arguing, Mike cancels a trip to the theme park. Tyler offers up the perfect solution for no more arguments for the rest of the day. But trying a therapy session to ease the tension in the house, it only makes things worse.

10.title: The Lurgy
10.plot: With an illness spreading, May-Li is the next to fall victim. With Mike pathetically sneezing and groaning, May-Li's determined to show Mike that she doesn't need him to run Ashdene Ridge. As the workload increases, so do her symptoms. It all becomes too much and May-Li soon realises that she needs Mike's help. The discovery of a recipe hidden in Joseph's book sends him and Chloe on a mission to make the best chicken soup, and Floss does everything in her power to avoid the lurgy.

11.title: RyanMan
11.plot: Ryan's lies threaten to overwhelm him when he tries to take credit for a responsible act of heroism, and things escalate when he's asked to appear on the TV. And Tyler grows jealous when he sees Jody with another boy she met at the gym.

12.title: Holding Out for a Hero
12.plot: Someone knows that Ryan stole the watch, and he's determined to find out who's trying to blackmail him. Forced to ride a trike and dress up as a clown in front of the Mayoress, Ryan is embarrassed in front of everyone. With the burglary fresh in her mind, Taz is on edge as Floss looks for a way to help her friend. A lump of coal in the fruit bowl reveals a new truth about May-Li - she's pregnant.

13.title: Stuck
13.plot: Sasha's pushed to take extreme action when she finds herself stuck reliving the same day.

14.title: The Secret
14.plot: Joseph's determination to be perfect for a foster family forces him to reflect on his own past issues.

15.title: Bird's Song
15.plot: Bird's lack of confidence is put to the test while on a trip to a nature reserve.

16.title: Home
16.plot: Charlie has to face the reality of her Grandad's condition when he comes to visit the DG.

17.title: Faker
17.plot: Tyler takes drastic action in an effort to protect his mum from her new boyfriend.

18.title: Me, Myself and I
18.plot: Jody learns a lesson in selfishness when they're forced to tidy up an abandoned school.

19.title: Jay and Bird's Day Off
19.plot: Jay's ambitious plan to seize the day brings him face to face with the memories of his childhood.

20.title: Wasters
20.plot: Alex's work experience at Lily's cafe doesn't go as he planned.

21.title: Joyless Division
21.plot: Ashdene Ridge is pushed to the brink after an experiment splits up the boys and girls.

22.title: No Escaping
22.plot: Jody must decide between a future with Brandon or facing up to her feelings for Tyler.

23.title: To Have and Not to Hold
23.plot: Charlie is faced with a test when a visit to her grandad takes an unexpected turn.

24.title: Missing Presumed Single
24.plot: It's Mike's wedding day but, with the groom missing, everyone must unite to save the day.

-1.title: The Joseph and Taz Files
-1.plot: Joseph tries to video a comet, but captures strange midnight activity instead. He's convinced it can all be explained by science, but Taz believes it's a ghost. How will they solve the mystery?

imdb.plot outline: Spin-off from the British hit TV series The Story Of Tracy Beaker based on the best-selling novel by Jaqueline Wilson. Set in a children's home known as the "dumping ground" the children face many fun adventures together as they grow up in foster care. Nevertheless this is a fab, fun-filled show packed with lots of great adventures.
imdb.title: The Dumping Ground
plot: Spin-off from the British hit TV series The Story Of Tracy Beaker based on the best-selling novel by Jaqueline Wilson. Set in a children's home known as the "dumping ground" the children face many fun adventures together as they grow up in foster care. Nevertheless this is a fab, fun-filled show packed with lots of great adventures.
A group of children who live together in a children's care home and together they face the challenges of living together in a modern foster home, and learn valuable life lessons.::Rosa Williams
